locality: Rubeho Mountains, Mafwemera Forest Reserve, ca. 5 km NNW of Mbuga Village, near top of small NE-facing valley in open, mostly herbaceous vegetation.
Along Singida-Babati rd, 1.8 km from Hanang Dist boundary, then downslope several 100 m. Bouldery slope with thinned woody cover, mostly Commiphora schimperi, & (now) smothered with Ipomoea vines.
9 km along rd from Makiungu to Misughaa, then 3 km along new rd to Mnane. Rugged S-facing escarpment slopes. Woodland 15(-20)m dominated by Brachystegia microphylla.
T5. Dodoma District: 3 miles on Kilimatinde-Dodoma rd.
